snippet.textDisplay:
pls forgive for any mistakes in the translation:
oh! Lord Krishna

Under the shade of kadam tree,
with all his cattle,
kanha plays the flute

along the banks of Yamuna river,
lord krishna is playing the flute
mother Yashoda has heard him now

O lord krishna,
where will you run today?
to Yamuna riverside?
to the shade of kadam tree?
Mother Yashoda will catch you,
and will tie you to a tree.

In the fields of vrindavan,
krishna's cows are grazing,
while he is enjoying playing his flute.
On hearing the sound of his flute,
gopis lose all their senses and get immersed into the music.

snippet.textDisplay:
Watched this song on the strong recommendation of  some of my young spirited friends. Though the feeling was not entirely traditional due to the loudness of all the western instruments but understandably that is because of the demand of the platform. It is highly praiseworthy of u Papon to highlight the beautiful tokari form of music in this platform. Hope more and more young folks will be drawn towards the richness of their culture due to songs like these. You are a braveheart who love this beautiful land. My love and blessings to you. 

I strongly believe someday people will be mesmerised by the singing of these glorious songs in their original earthy style san all the heavy instruments in one of such popular platforms by someone like u...
